The paper discusses planning applications involving complex relationships defined on high-dimensional, continuous variables, which is a common problem in robotics. Therefore, cs.AI and cs.RO are the most likely categories. The paper also extends the STRIPS planning language, which falls under the category of planning and scheduling (cs.PL). The paper also discusses cost-sensitive planning, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with declarative specifications and blackbox samplers, which are related to symbolic reasoning and knowledge representation (cs.SY).
